geneVariantDescriptions.description: ROS1 G2032R lies within the protein kinase domain of the Ros1 protein (UniProt.org). G2032R has been associated with resistance to Ros1 tyrosine kinase inhibitors in the context of ROS1 fusions in patients (PMID: 23724914, PMID: 25033171, PMID: 29477381), but has not been biochemically characterized and therefore, its effect on Ros1 protein function is unknown (PubMed, Feb 2020).

references.title: Acquired resistance to crizotinib from a mutation in CD74-ROS1.
